  "texts": [
    "From the definition of the adjacency tensor of order m, we can define the generalized density of m-hyperedges, δ (m) as the ratio between the number of 2-hyperedges that are present in the hypergraph and the number of possible 2-hyperedges:",
    "The hyperedges to which node i belongs determine which nodes interact or not with i, and thus which nodes influence or not its dynamics.",
    "In the case of a simple graph, each link of node i connects it to a distinct neighbor.",
    "Conversely, in a hypergraph, a node i with two or more hyperedges of order m ≥ 2 can share one or more neighboring nodes with different hyperedges.",
    "Figure 1a-c shows three different configurations for a node with four 2-hyperedges."
  ],
